      "message": "rmp-\u003echassis_id_len was set to vec_len(n-\u003echassis_id) on line 147, here the clib_min compares it against vec_len(n-\u003echassis_id) thus becoming a noop. If vec_len(chassis_id) \u003e sizeof(rmp-\u003echassis_id), this will overflow. Same is true for port_id logic on lines 150 and 151. Looking at LLDP_MAX_CHASS_ID_LEN/LLDP_MAX_PORT_ID_LEN \u003d 255 the API message is lacking - it only supports 64 bytes. We should increase it (in .api definition) to 255 to be able to hold full peer-received data.\n\nCompare with system_name on line 153-4 correctly using vec_len vs sizeof.",
