      "side": 1,
      "message": "While these memsets are good, they\u0027re not enough. ﻿﻿REPLY_MACRO_DETAILS4_END allocates via vl_msg_api_alloc which does not zero - so the handler deliberately clib_memsets mgmt_ip4, mgmt_ip6, mgmt_oid, port_desc — but not system_name[256], chassis_id[64], or port_id[64], which are only partially filled (clib_min(vec_len, ...) bytes). The uninitialized remainder leaks prior heap contents to the API client.\n\nI\u0027d zero the whole rmp once up front, to be on the safe side. It\u0027s also simpler and future-proof if any more fields are ever added.",
